WEBVTT

00:08.440 --> 00:10.101
- NO!

00:10.140 --> 00:11.539
NO, THAT IS NOT ACCEPTABLE.
WE HAD A DEAL.

00:11.570 --> 00:13.401
DOES THAT NOT MEAN ANYTHING
TO ANYBODY ANYMORE?

00:13.440 --> 00:15.579
WHAT, YOUR YES, NOT YES?
YOUR NO, NOT NO?

00:15.610 --> 00:17.441
I MEAN, IF THIS DOESN'T
GO THROUGH, I'M SCREWED.

00:17.480 --> 00:18.401
I'M SCREWED.

00:18.450 --> 00:24.480
I'VE GOT A MORTGAGE,
I HAVE A BABY, COME ON!

00:24.520 --> 00:25.680
OH, GEEZ.

00:30.790 --> 00:35.250
NO, LET ME CALL YOU BACK,
LET ME CALL YOU BACK.

00:48.180 --> 00:51.570
YOU ALL RIGHT?

00:51.610 --> 00:52.372
- BETTER THAN YOU, BEAMER.

00:52.420 --> 00:55.719
- WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

01:03.560 --> 01:07.189
- WELL, NOW THIS SITUATION
IS ALL WRONG.

01:07.230 --> 01:08.754
- OH, COME ON.

01:14.470 --> 01:18.861
- TRUST ME,
I'M DOING THESE GLASSES A FAVOR.

01:18.910 --> 01:19.729
- UNH!

01:19.780 --> 01:22.271
- TAKING THE LADY
TO A SPA WEEKEND.

01:22.310 --> 01:23.277
WHAAAT?

01:23.310 --> 01:24.800
THAT'S BIG TIME, SON.

01:24.850 --> 01:26.442
- HE WOULDN'T EVEN TELL ME
HOW MUCH IT COSTS.

01:26.480 --> 01:28.414
- THAT'S BECAUSE
IT'S NOT ABOUT MONEY, JULES.

01:28.450 --> 01:31.146
IT'S ABOUT GIVING YOU A VACATION
YOU SO RICHLY DESERVE.

01:31.190 --> 01:33.408
AND SPENDING AN ABSURD
AMOUNT OF MONEY TO DO IT.

01:33.460 --> 01:35.758
- YOU ARE GROWING UP
RIGHT IN FRONT OF MY EYES.

01:35.790 --> 01:37.678
- COME ON, GUS,
YOU KNEW THIS DAY WOULD COME.

01:37.730 --> 01:38.685
- YEAH.

01:38.730 --> 01:40.789
- BYE, GUS.

01:40.830 --> 01:42.764
- OKAY.

01:42.800 --> 01:44.495
MAKE SURE YOU WATER MY PLANTS,
THRICE DAILY.

01:44.530 --> 01:46.634
BUT DO NOT TALK TO THEM,
BECAUSE ONCE THEY GET STARTED

01:46.670 --> 01:48.467
THEY WILL NOT STOP,
ESPECIALLY JIM.

01:48.500 --> 01:49.535
- JIM IS THE FICHUS?
- YES, INDEED.

01:49.570 --> 01:52.539
- GOT IT.

01:52.580 --> 01:53.808
WHAT?

01:53.840 --> 01:56.343
- I NEED TO
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

01:58.480 --> 01:59.549
- I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO DO THAT.

01:59.580 --> 02:00.911
- YES, YOU DO.
- NO.

02:00.950 --> 02:03.180
- READY?

02:03.220 --> 02:07.281
- FINE.

02:07.320 --> 02:08.480
WAFFLES.

02:08.520 --> 02:10.829
- MY GOD, IT'S CRAZY, THAT'S
EXACTLY WHAT I WAS THINKING.

02:10.860 --> 02:12.521
THAT WAS JUST A TEST.
- OKAY.

02:12.560 --> 02:16.599
- OKAY, HERE IT IS, READY?
- ALL RIGHT.

02:16.630 --> 02:18.518
STILL WAFFLES.
- DAMN IT.

02:18.570 --> 02:20.538
ONE MORE TIME.
- OKAY.

02:24.310 --> 02:26.505
- WHY ARE YOU GAZING
INTO EACH OTHER'S EYES?

02:26.540 --> 02:29.907
- WE'RE NOT DOING THAT,
JUST A ROUTINE FOREHEAD CHECK.

02:29.950 --> 02:33.340
RECIPROCATED.

02:33.380 --> 02:34.608
- LISTEN, SHAWN,
I KNOW YOU'RE NERVOUS

02:34.650 --> 02:36.208
ABOUT THIS WEEKEND,
BUT DON'T WORRY.

02:36.250 --> 02:37.478
YOU'RE READY FOR THIS.

02:37.520 --> 02:40.580
NOW GO AND HAVE SOME FUN,
YOU BIG SPENDER, WHAT?

02:40.620 --> 02:42.588
COME ON, SON, COME ON.

02:42.630 --> 02:44.279
- I'M GONNA CALL YOU, OKAY?
SO KEEP YOUR PHONE ON.

02:44.330 --> 02:47.652
- OH, YEAH.

02:47.700 --> 02:50.191
- THINK YOU CAN SURVIVE
FOR TWO DAYS WITHOUT EACH OTHER?

02:50.230 --> 02:52.232
- OF COURSE.
- [laughs]

02:52.270 --> 02:55.535
- LOOK, JULES, I KNOW THAT YOU
HAVE VERY DEFINITE EXPECTATIONS

02:55.570 --> 02:56.537
FOR THIS WEEKEND.

02:56.570 --> 02:57.559
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

02:57.610 --> 02:58.804
- WELL, YOU SENT ME AN EMAIL ON
THE FIFTH SAYING

02:58.840 --> 03:02.640
"SHAWN, I HAVE VERY DEFINITE
EXPECTATIONS FOR THIS WEEKEND."

03:02.680 --> 03:04.671
- RIGHT,
TO WHICH YOU RESPONDED,

03:04.710 --> 03:07.270
"SLUMBER PARTY,
NUDIE TIMES, DRINKY-DRINKY."

03:07.320 --> 03:09.447
- THAT'S MY
"OUT OF OFFICE REPLY."

03:09.490 --> 03:11.947
- LOOK, I JUST THINK
THIS TRIP IS IMPORTANT FOR US.

03:11.990 --> 03:14.458
IT'S OUR FIRST TIME
OUT OF THE SBPD BUBBLE

03:14.490 --> 03:15.752
AND WE'LL SEE HOW WE
REALLY ARE AS A COUPLE.

03:15.790 --> 03:16.859
- MMMMMMMM!

03:16.890 --> 03:18.380
- IT IS AN OPPORTUNITY FOR US

03:18.430 --> 03:19.658
TO TAKE OUR RELATIONSHIP
TO THE NEXT STEP

03:19.700 --> 03:21.292
IN A MATURE WAY.

03:21.330 --> 03:22.729
- I'M VERY EXCITED.
- ME TOO.

03:22.770 --> 03:25.762
NOW LET'S GO HAVE FUN.

03:31.510 --> 03:34.604
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME,
I HAVE AN EPIC WEEKEND PLANNED.

03:34.640 --> 03:35.971
IT'S GONNA BE OFF THE--

03:36.010 --> 03:40.515
[tires squealing]

03:40.550 --> 03:44.247
- HOOK.

03:44.290 --> 03:45.712
[sighs]

03:45.750 --> 03:48.719
[All By Myself instrumental]

03:48.760 --> 03:54.756
*

04:02.370 --> 04:03.667
- WHOA.

04:03.710 --> 04:06.873
HELLO, GUSTER.
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU SHOPPED HERE.

04:06.910 --> 04:08.673
- I HAD COUPONS.
- YES.

04:08.710 --> 04:10.541
THEY DO HAVE
SOME GOOD BARGAINS.

04:10.580 --> 04:12.514
I LOADED UP
ON AN ARMFUL OF 40 WA'I'I'S.

04:12.550 --> 04:13.915
THAT'S A LOT
OF LIGHT BULBS.

04:13.950 --> 04:15.440
- YEAH.

04:15.480 --> 04:17.846
YEAH, I'M SET.

04:17.890 --> 04:20.779
GOOD LORD, YOU'RE NOT ACTUALLY
BUYING SCENTED CANDLES ARE YOU?

04:20.820 --> 04:22.685
- HOW ELSE AM I SUPPOSED TO
FRESHEN UP MY PLACE?

04:22.730 --> 04:23.526
- WELL, DO WHAT I DO,

04:23.560 --> 04:25.619
YOU PUT YOUR
LAUNDRY BASKET OUTSIDE,

04:25.660 --> 04:26.957
AND BLAST THE PLACE
WITH RIGHT GUARD.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.524
- YOUR GIRLFRIEND'S GONNA WISH
SHE STAYED IN PRISON.

04:28.560 --> 04:30.494
DON'T YOU USUALLY
SEE HER ON SATURDAYS?

04:30.530 --> 04:32.589
- YEAH, BUT SHE GOT
THROWN IN SOLITARY

04:32.640 --> 04:35.393
FOR DRY-GULCHING
A HOME GIRL ON THE CHOW LINE.

04:35.440 --> 04:38.898
[laughs]
SHE SURE HATES CUTSIES.

04:38.940 --> 04:40.601
- SHAWN AND I
USUALLY PLAY SKEE-BALL,

04:40.640 --> 04:42.540
AND MAKE CRANK CALLS
ALL NIGHT.

04:42.580 --> 04:44.605
- THAT'S YOU WHO
KEEPS CALLING ME?

04:44.650 --> 04:46.948
- NO.

04:46.980 --> 04:48.618
- WHAT THE--?

04:48.650 --> 04:49.787
HENRY?

04:49.820 --> 04:51.481
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

04:51.520 --> 04:52.987
- BUY ONE FULL PRICE,
GET ONE FREE.

04:53.020 --> 04:54.578
THAT'S WHAT I CALL VALUE.

04:54.620 --> 04:58.420
OH, SO YOU'RE THE ONE THAT
TOOK ALL THE LIGHT BULBS, HUH?

04:58.460 --> 05:00.018
YOU TWO SHOP TOGETHER OFI'EN?

05:00.060 --> 05:01.618
- PFF, PLEASE.
- NO.

05:01.660 --> 05:03.025
- COME ON, MAN.

05:03.070 --> 05:05.322
- SO YOU AND YOUR SHIRTS
GOT A BIG WEEKEND PLANNED?

05:05.370 --> 05:08.567
- IF BY BIG WEEKEND YOU MEAN
WATCHING THE MANNIX MARATHON,

05:08.600 --> 05:09.862
THEN YES, WE DO.

05:09.910 --> 05:11.537
- YEAH, WE GOT
NOTHING TO DO EITHER.

05:11.570 --> 05:13.470
- TSK, SPEAK FOR YOURSELF.
I HAVE PLANS.

05:13.510 --> 05:15.501
IN FACT, I'M GOING
TO A NEW SPOT TONIGHT.

05:15.540 --> 05:16.768
IT'S SUPPOSED
TO BE SLAMMIN'.

05:16.810 --> 05:18.072
PACKED TO THE RAFI'ERS
WITH "BIDDIES."

05:18.110 --> 05:20.749
HEH, HEH.

05:20.780 --> 05:21.712
LADIES.

05:21.750 --> 05:22.842
- OH.

05:22.890 --> 05:25.017
WELL, PERSONALLY
I'M LOOKING FORWARD

05:25.050 --> 05:27.382
TO A NICE, QUIET
WEEKEND AT HOME, ALONE.

05:27.420 --> 05:28.956
- YEAH, SOLITUDE.

05:28.990 --> 05:30.457
GOOD FOR THE SOUL.

05:30.490 --> 05:33.755
- GOOD FOR YOU.

05:33.800 --> 05:35.392
- PACKED TO THE RAFI'ERS?

05:35.430 --> 05:38.422
- YEAH.

05:47.640 --> 05:50.746
- EXCELLENT, NOW I'LL JUST NEED
TO SEE A PHOTO I.D., MR. GUSTER.

05:50.780 --> 05:52.919
- CERTAINLY.

05:56.690 --> 06:00.114
- ENJOY YOUR STAY.
- I AM SURE WE WILL.

06:00.160 --> 06:03.084
OH...

06:03.130 --> 06:05.121
THAT'S ALL YOU.

06:05.160 --> 06:06.752
[sighs]

06:06.800 --> 06:10.497
- SHAWN, THE HOTEL CAN ARRANGE
FOR A HOT AIR BALLOON TOUR.

06:10.530 --> 06:11.599
I WOULD LOVE
TO DO THAT.

06:11.630 --> 06:13.939
- I THINK IT WOULD ALSO
BE ROMANTIC IF WE TOOK NAPS

06:13.970 --> 06:15.858
IN THOSE LARGE POOL FLOATIES
THAT LOOK LIKE SHAMU.

06:15.900 --> 06:18.061
- SHAWN, I KNOW THIS
ISN'T YOUR THING,

06:18.110 --> 06:20.829
BUT IT MAKES ME SO HAPPY
THAT YOU'RE HERE.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.609
AND LOOK, WE DID IT!
- [laughs]

06:22.650 --> 06:24.504
- THE TWO OF US,
ON VACATION.

06:24.550 --> 06:27.713
- ALONG WITH ALL OF THESE
OTHER PEOPLE, UNFORTUNATELY.

06:27.750 --> 06:29.547
- WE'RE GOING TO HAVE FUN,
RELAX, AND MOST IMPORTANTLY,

06:29.590 --> 06:30.340
NO WORK.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.449
FOR TWO WHOLE DAYS
I AM NOT A COP,

06:32.490 --> 06:33.650
AND YOU ARE
NOT A PSYCHIC.

06:33.690 --> 06:35.783
- COME ON, YOU KNOW I CAN'T
JUST TURN IT OFF LIKE THAT.

06:35.820 --> 06:37.048
- OKAY.

06:37.090 --> 06:41.049
BUT JUST--NONE OF THIS?

06:41.100 --> 06:42.089
- HEH, HEH!

06:48.570 --> 06:51.562
- I BELIEVE THIS IS GONNA
WORK OUT JUST FINE, SUGAR PLUM.

06:51.610 --> 06:54.499
- LET'S GO A HUNTIN'.
- OOH.

06:59.580 --> 07:03.016
[The Friendly Indians'
I Know You Know]

07:03.050 --> 07:05.018
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

07:05.050 --> 07:07.086
* THAT I'M NOT
TELLING THE TRUTH *

07:07.120 --> 07:08.451
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

07:08.490 --> 07:10.082
* THEY JUST DON'T
HAVE ANY PROOF *

07:10.130 --> 07:12.086
* EMBRACE THE DECEPTION

07:12.130 --> 07:13.620
* LEARN HOW TO BEND

07:13.660 --> 07:15.196
* YOUR WORST INHIBITIONS

07:15.230 --> 07:17.698
* TEND TO PSYCH YOU OUT
IN THE END *

07:24.640 --> 07:26.528
- COME ON.

07:26.580 --> 07:27.399
[sighs]

07:27.440 --> 07:30.000
LOOK, GUS,
THIS IS MY FIFI'H MESSAGE.

07:30.050 --> 07:31.199
I'M ALL OUT OF ALIAS'.

07:31.250 --> 07:33.172
IT'S SHAWN,
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

07:33.220 --> 07:36.212
CALL ME BACK IMMEDIAMENTE!

07:38.950 --> 07:41.350
GRACIAS.

07:45.230 --> 07:46.857
WHAT THE--WHAT?

07:46.900 --> 07:49.619
- [laughs]

07:49.670 --> 07:51.592
_ UM--
- OH, UM, SHAWN.

07:51.630 --> 07:54.497
THIS IS BARBIE AND CLIVE NOBLE,
THEY JUST ARRIVED TODAY AS WELL.

07:54.540 --> 07:55.393
- DID THEY?

07:55.440 --> 07:56.839
- YEAH, I SAW JULIET HERE,
AND I SAID,

07:56.870 --> 07:59.009
NOW THERE IS
A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN

07:59.040 --> 08:00.234
WITH IMPECCABLE TASTE.

08:00.280 --> 08:01.838
WE'RE GONNA
GET ALONG JUST FINE.

08:01.880 --> 08:02.869
[laughter]

08:02.910 --> 08:04.070
OH, MY GOD,
LOOK AT THAT ROCK.

08:04.110 --> 08:05.975
- OH, YEAH.

08:06.010 --> 08:07.568
- SORRY WE
STOLE YOUR SHADE, SHAWN.

08:07.620 --> 08:08.609
- UH...

08:08.650 --> 08:10.049
- OH, NO, NO, NO, IT'S FINE,
WE CAN SHARE MINE.

08:10.090 --> 08:11.216
- I DID SAY "SEAT SAVE."

08:11.250 --> 08:13.013
DO YOU NOT REMEMBER ME
SAYING "SEAT SAVE?"

08:13.060 --> 08:14.254
- NO, I DON'T.

08:14.290 --> 08:16.087
- [laughs] OH!

08:16.120 --> 08:18.759
- [laughs]

08:18.790 --> 08:20.052
- WHY ARE YOU INVITING STRANGERS
INTO OUR VACATION?

08:20.100 --> 08:22.091
- BECAUSE THAT IS
WHAT ADULT COUPLES DO,

08:22.130 --> 08:23.290
THEY MAKE VACATION FRIENDS.

08:23.330 --> 08:25.628
- WHY DO WE NEED NEW FRIENDS?
I HAVE GUS.

08:25.670 --> 08:26.989
YOU HAVE...
WHOEVER YOUR FRIENDS ARE.

08:27.040 --> 08:30.066
- SHAWN, YOU'RE EMBARRASSING ME.

08:30.110 --> 08:32.260
SO, UH, BARBIE HERE
IS FROM KENTUCKY

08:32.310 --> 08:34.301
AND SHE MET CLIVE IN SEATTLE
AND THEY HAVE BEEN MARRIED

08:34.340 --> 08:35.602
FOR FIVE YEARS.

08:35.640 --> 08:38.200
- WOW, THAT'S
SO MUCH INFORMATION,

08:38.250 --> 08:40.241
HOW LONG WAS I
AT THE JUICE BAR?

08:40.280 --> 08:41.679
- SO, UH, WHAT
DO YOU DO, SHAWN?

08:41.720 --> 08:43.540
- PROFESSIONAL WATER SKIER.

08:43.590 --> 08:44.579
- WHO WORKS FOR
THE CITY OF SANTA BARBARA,

08:44.620 --> 08:45.985
AS DO I.

08:46.020 --> 08:48.750
- Y'ALL BOTH WATER SKI
FOR THE CITY OF SANTA BARBARA?

08:48.790 --> 08:50.724
OH, BABY--
MY TEMPLES, MY TEMPLES.

08:50.760 --> 08:52.318
- OH, SORRY, HONEY.

08:52.360 --> 08:53.725
- OH, OH!
- HOW'S THAT?

08:53.760 --> 08:55.159
- OH, RIGHT THERE, MM.

08:55.200 --> 08:57.327
- SO, UM, IS THERE
A LOT OF MONEY

08:57.370 --> 08:58.621
IN COMPETITIVE
AQUATICS, SHAWN?

08:58.670 --> 08:59.329
- IT'S GOOD BENEFITS.

08:59.370 --> 09:00.689
DECENT CHRISTMAS PARTY.

09:00.740 --> 09:01.866
YOU KNOW, WE DO OKAY.

09:01.900 --> 09:05.233
- OH, I BET.
THIS PLACE IS PUH-RICEY.

09:05.270 --> 09:06.976
- NOTHING TOO GOOD
FOR MY BARBIE.

09:07.010 --> 09:09.274
- OH, BABY, WHAT DO
I DO TO DESERVE YOU?

09:09.310 --> 09:11.699
- BESIDES TOTALLY DESERVE ME?
- OH, I DO.

09:11.750 --> 09:12.774
- MUAH, I LOVE YOU
SO MUCH, BABY.

09:12.820 --> 09:14.139
- I LOVE YOU.

09:14.180 --> 09:15.272
- [laughs]

09:15.320 --> 09:16.309
- I HATE THEM.

09:16.350 --> 09:17.908
- WELL, SHAWN,
THE NOBLES AND I

09:17.950 --> 09:19.349
WERE TALKING ABOUT
GRABBING DINNER TOGETHER.

09:19.390 --> 09:20.812
- GREAT, YOU SHOULD
ALL ENJOY YOURSELVES.

09:20.860 --> 09:21.815
- ALL OF US, TOGETHER.

09:21.860 --> 09:24.328
- MMMM, NO THANKS.

09:24.360 --> 09:25.850
- WE'D LOVE TO.
- SOUNDS GOOD.

09:25.890 --> 09:26.857
- YEAH.
- EXCELLENT.

09:26.900 --> 09:28.595
- ALL RIGHT.

09:28.630 --> 09:29.665
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S
GET THOSE STICKY BUNS

09:29.700 --> 09:30.291
INTO A MUD BATH,
BABY, COME ON.

09:30.330 --> 09:31.695
- OH!

09:31.730 --> 09:33.288
- COME ON, LET'S GO.
- WOULD YOU STOP IT?

09:33.340 --> 09:35.035
- WE'LL SEE YOU GUYS.

09:35.070 --> 09:36.332
- WHAT'S YOUR DAMAGE, SPENCER?

09:36.370 --> 09:38.065
- WHAT IS MY DAMAGE?

09:38.110 --> 09:41.079
I'M GONE FIVE MINUTES AND
ALL OF A SUDDEN WE'RE SWINGERS?

09:41.110 --> 09:43.146
WHAT IS THIS, THE ICE STORM?
WHO ARE THOSE PEOPLE?

09:43.180 --> 09:44.602
- THEY'RE JUST PEOPLE.

09:44.650 --> 09:46.106
- THAT'S THE WORST KIND!

09:46.150 --> 09:48.243
WE DON'T KNOW THEM,
SOMETHING'S OFF.

09:48.280 --> 09:49.679
PLUS, WE DON'T KNOW THEM.

09:49.720 --> 09:50.812
AND WE'LL HAVE
TO TALK TO THEM.

09:50.850 --> 09:53.216
- IT'S CALLED
BEING AN ADULT, SHAWN.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.353
YOU SHOULD
TRY IT SOMETIME.

09:55.390 --> 09:57.722
- I'M WEARING A MAN'S ROBE.

09:57.760 --> 09:58.829
[upbeat club music]

09:58.860 --> 09:59.997
- WHAT DID I TELL YOU?

10:00.030 --> 10:02.794
BIDDIES BY THE BUSHEL.

10:02.830 --> 10:03.967
OOH!

10:04.000 --> 10:05.888
I'M ABOUT TO
PUT IN SOME WORK!

10:05.930 --> 10:08.637
- I'LL TELL YA,
IF I WEREN'T IN A SERIOUS

10:08.670 --> 10:11.662
AND MEANINGFUL RELATIONSHIP
I'D BE DOING ALL SORTS OF DAMAGE

10:11.710 --> 10:13.769
UP IN THIS HIZZY.

10:13.810 --> 10:15.835
AM I SAYING THAT RIGHT?

10:15.880 --> 10:16.904
HIZZY?

10:16.950 --> 10:18.372
- WHAT ARE YOU GUYS SAYING?

10:18.410 --> 10:20.048
- LASSIE, YOU ONLY THINK YOU
GOT GAME 'CAUSE YOU GOT A LADY.

10:20.080 --> 10:22.412
- NO, NO, NO, NO, I GOT
A LADY BECAUSE I GOT GAME!

10:22.450 --> 10:24.315
- PLEASE, YOU WOULDN'T
BE ABLE TO GET ANY KIND OF PLAY

10:24.350 --> 10:25.214
INSIDE THIS ROOM.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.411
- I CAN GET MORE
PLAY THAN YOU, PLAYA!

10:27.460 --> 10:29.155
I MEAN, DON'T
GET ME WRONG, GUS,

10:29.190 --> 10:30.885
YOU HAVE A CERTAIN
SORT OF CHARM ABOUT YOU,

10:30.930 --> 10:32.898
BUT I'M A CLASSIC.

10:32.930 --> 10:36.058
I NEVER GO OUT OF STYLE,
I'M LIKE PLEATED PANTS.

10:36.100 --> 10:37.067
- REALLY?

10:37.100 --> 10:38.192
CARE TO MAKE
THIS INTERESTING?

10:38.230 --> 10:40.198
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

10:40.240 --> 10:41.264
I CAN'T HEAR SQUAT.

10:41.300 --> 10:43.359
- WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
A LITTLE GENTLEMEN'S WAGER

10:43.410 --> 10:45.833
OVER WHO CAN STRIKE FIRST
WITH THE LADIES.

10:45.870 --> 10:47.235
- GREAT!
I WANT IN.

10:47.280 --> 10:49.009
- [laughs] I DON'T THINK SO.

10:49.040 --> 10:52.271
- WHAT? HEY, LISTEN,
I'M AS YOUNG ON THE INSIDE

10:52.310 --> 10:54.244
AS TH ESE KIDS ARE
ON THE OUTSIDE.

10:54.280 --> 10:55.679
- YEAH, BUT WHEN YOU WERE
THAT YOUNG ON THE OUTSIDE,

10:55.720 --> 10:56.982
THIS WAS ALL FARM LAND.

10:57.020 --> 10:57.839
- HA!

10:57.890 --> 10:59.312
- HEY, YOU WANNA
PUT IT TO THE TEST?

10:59.350 --> 11:00.988
HOW ABOUT THIS?

11:01.020 --> 11:04.148
FIRST ONE TO PULL SOME DIGITS
OFF ONE OF THESE HO'I'I'IES WINS.

11:04.190 --> 11:06.283
LOSERS BRING BARBECUE
TO MY HOUSE ON SUNDAY.

11:06.330 --> 11:07.922
- OH, IT IS SO ON.

11:07.960 --> 11:08.949
- YEAH, IT IS!

11:09.000 --> 11:10.262
- SAFETY IS OFF.

11:10.300 --> 11:11.699
